news.title: China's new home prices fell for fourth month in November 2022
news.para: New home prices fell 0.2% from October, the fourth straight decline, and by 1.6% from a year earlier, the seventh on-year drop, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data.

news.title: The Economic Times Real Estate Awards 2022-East rewards excellence in industry
news.para: The second edition of The Economic Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2022 – East was graced by the presence of chief guest Debashis Sen, MD, WBHIDCO and Chairman, NKDA & NDITA.

news.title: Large residential builders to log double-digit growth in FY24: Crisil
news.para: CRISIL Ratings expects residential prices to rise 6-10% this fiscal and a further 3-5% in the next fiscal across the top six cities i.e Mumbai Metropolitan Region, National Capital Region, Bengaluru, Pune, Hyderabad, and Kolkata.

news.title: Pune civic body rolls out redevelopment plan for quarters housing its staffers
news.para: The civic administration has planned redevelopment of two municipal buildings in Nana Peth. Nearly 100 houses will be built by spending around Rs 15 crore.

news.title: Residents of Lucknow development body-run flats grapple with maintenance problems
news.para: Maintenance of these apartments is still under LDA as residents’ welfare associations (RWAs) are yet to be constituted. Residents, however, claim that the LDA authorities have shut their eyes towards their grievances.

news.title: GIS: Indore development body to provide details of property to investors
news.para: “We have a building on Super Corridor that has been renovated and decorated to provide information regarding our four major schemes — 169-A, 169-B, 151 and TPS 10,” the authority CEO RP Ahirwar told TOI.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body achieves only half of property tax target of FY23
news.para: Nilesh Deshmukh, head of the tax department, PCMC, said that around 40% (2.32 lakh) property holders are unreachable through mail and their properties are not linked with their mobile numbers.

news.title: Ludhiana development body razes seven illegal colonies, civic body flattens two buildings
news.para: The buildings were situated on Chaar Khamba road in Model Town, Model Town-Jawaddi road and near New Krishna Mandir in Model Town extension.

news.title: Property owners fret as technology glitches hold up registries at tehsil offices in Gurugram
news.para: There are six tehsils - Gurugram, Manesar, Pataudi, Farukhnagar, Sohna and Wazirabad - and three sub-tehsils - Harsaru, Kadipur and Badshapur - in the city.

news.title: Yamuna Expressway authority registers FIR against 50 for developing illegal colonies in Tappal
news.para: On November 9, YEIDA carried out the demolition drive in Tappal and freed over 15 hectares of land, the market price of which is pegged at Rs 230 crore.

news.title: Submit plan to clear illegal colonies in Noida along Hindon banks, agencies told
news.para: The four agencies will also have to make plans to increase the green cover in the Hindon floodplains under the provisions of the Noida and Greater Noida master plans.

news.title: Gurugram: Residents demand structural & financial audits of New Town Heights
news.para: In a letter to DTCP director general TL Satyaprakash, deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav and district town planner Amit Madholia, residents have alleged that poor design and construction flaws pose a safety risk to 600 families living in the society.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth 78 crore in Heera Gold scam
news.para: ED sleuths stumbled upon Nowhera Sheik and her Heera Group of companies transferring 148 crore to SA Builders and Developers for purchasing properties in Tolichowki.

news.title: Poonawalla Fincorp sells housing finance arm to TPG for Rs 3,900 crore
news.para: ​The transaction, subject to regulatory approvals, is being carried out by TPG global arm Perseus SG, the statement said, adding the deal will is part of its effort to maximise shareholder value and to focus on consumer and MSME financing by building a tech-led financial services company.

news.title: MahaRERA asks 13 districts to ensure buyers get Rs 730 crore in compensations
news.para: ​The Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRera) has also appointed a retired additional district collector to follow-up in such cases where dues have been pending, an official statement said.
